  "prompt": "Where can you buy Lego blocks all in the same color?",
  "response": "You can purchase LEGO blocks all in the same color from several sources:\n\n1. **LEGO Official Site**: The LEGO Build a Minifigure station allows you to select specific pieces and colors. You can also find limited edition sets that feature blocks in a single color.\n\n2. **BrickLink**: This is a marketplace specifically for LEGO products. You can find sellers offering individual bricks in various colors. You can filter by color to find blocks that match your needs.\n\n3. **Brick Owl**: Similar to BrickLink, this website lets you buy individual LEGO pieces from multiple sellers, where you can apply filtering options to find bricks in the same color.\n\n4. **eBay**: You can often find bulk listings of LEGO bricks sorted by color. Just search for the specific color you want.\n\n5. **Amazon**: Some sellers offer sets or bulk lots of LEGO bricks in specific colors. Check for third-party sellers.\n\n6. **Local LEGO Stores or Toy Stores**: Some physical LEGO stores have a Pick a Brick wall where you can select bricks in specific colors.\n\n7. **Custom LEGO Sets**: Some companies or sellers create custom sets featuring bricks in a single color, available through websites like Etsy.\n\nWhen buying, make sure to check the quantity and condition of the bricks (new or used) to ensure they meet your expectations!",
